(Krishitantra Repository - Full Architecture and Code Explanation) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Purpose of this report) Tj
T*
(- Explain architecture and runtime flow.) Tj
T*
(- Explain every repository file and every function in source code files.) Tj
T*
(- Explain why each approach/tool is used, and why alternatives were not used.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1\) System architecture \(high level\)) Tj
T*
(- Frontend: static single-page dashboard in frontend/index.html + frontend/app.js +) Tj
T*
(frontend/styles.css.) Tj
T*
(- Backend: FastAPI app in backend/app/main.py exposing inference, telemetry, analysis, evolution,) Tj
T*
(registry, drift, governance, metrics.) Tj
T*
(- Model runtime: TinyLlama GGUF via llama-cpp-python in backend/app/model.py.) Tj
T*
(- Persistence: SQLite in backend/data/requests.db via backend/app/database.py.) Tj
T*
(- Evolution pipeline: backend/app/evolution/*.py.) Tj
T*
(- Governance and rollback: backend/app/governance.py + backend/app/evolution/rollback.py.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why this architecture \(and not heavier alternatives\)) Tj
T*
(- FastAPI + static frontend is simple and fast for local/demo ops; not using React/Next avoids build) Tj
T*
(complexity and deployment overhead.) Tj
T*
(- GGUF + llama-cpp runs local quantized inference with low memory; not using full PyTorch runtime) Tj
T*
(avoids heavy GPU dependency.) Tj
T*
(- SQLite is enough for local telemetry/audit with low ops overhead; not PostgreSQL avoids) Tj
T*
(infrastructure burden.) Tj
T*
(- Evolution is simulated/metadata-driven for GGUF because GGUF binaries are not straightforward for) Tj
T*
(in-place structural retraining.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2\) End-to-end runtime flow) Tj
T*
(A\) Inference flow) Tj
T*
(1. User sends chat from frontend/app.js sendMessage\(\).) Tj
T*
(2. POST /infer in backend/app/main.py.) Tj
T*
(3. main.py calls model.generate_text\(\).) Tj
T*
(4. model.py generates response with llama_cpp and simulated telemetry.) Tj
T*
(5. drift_detector.detect_drift\(\) computes drift score.) Tj
T*
(6. database.py logs request, structural telemetry, drift event.) Tj
T*
(7. If drift threshold exceeded, background evolution trigger starts.) Tj
T*
(8. Response returned to UI with request_id, latency, drift info.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(B\) Evolution flow) Tj
T*
(1. /evolve or auto-trigger calls run_evolution_cycle\(\) in orchestrator.py.) Tj
T*
(2. Reads usage_and_structural_report.json.) Tj
T*
(3. Generates candidate prune plans.) Tj
T*
(4. Scores candidates.) Tj
T*
(5. Backs up current optimized model.) Tj
T*
(6. Recompiles simulated optimized version \(new vN folder\).) Tj
T*
(7. Validates model \(similarity, factual checks, latency\).) Tj
T*
(8. PASS => register in model registry; FAIL => rollback.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3\) File-by-file details) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
ET
endstream
endobj
